      "type": "code",
      "id": "a4299cb2950ce0d1",
      "text": "let\n  emacsFlake = import (builtins.fetchGit {\n    url = \"https://github.com/nix-community/emacs-overlay.git\";\n    rev = \"3a2a3f3c3b8e1e36a9b939e5c6e5d8f41e6ddee7\";\n    sha256 = \"1r5y6z9l7sqxn6z5f7c24rd6hbz7fjn0l0z8bvqz9a9lx0jz1bz\";\n  });\nin\n  emacsFlake.emacs\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "104b49d3f5fcbfe9",
      "text": "Run nix flake init to create a new flake in the current directory"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "a5204712d1f352c0",
      "text": "[…] [[Frank Beu]]'s emacs-flake [https://github.com/FrankBeu/emacs-flake/blob/main/README.org github] is a flake that allows users to easily install and use a specific version of [[Emacs]], along with any desired packages and configuration, using the Nix package manager. It provides a simple, reproducible way of managing emacs environments, and allows for easy switching between different versions and configurations of emacs. The README provides instructions on how to use the flake, including how to install emacs, how to add packages and configuration, and how to switch between different emacs environments. Additionally, it also contains links to additional resources and troubleshooting tips."
